member.name: T:ApiTestGenerator.Models.ApiDocs.ApiSet
member.summary:
This class defines a Model used for translating various different web based API calls between the different formats. It is based on the Open API Specification. The idea is to allow an engine to populate this model with information from sources like:
An OAS document
An Http Archive (HAR) file.
A Postman request collection.
and turn the results into a test harness that can be executed.

Tools that do not recognize a specific format MAY default back to the type alone, as if the format is not specified.

member.name: T:ApiTestGenerator.Models.Consts.ParserTokens
member.summary: This class contains constant string values that are used for parsing OAS documents.
member.remarks:
These string constants represent a few different types of 'searchable' strings. The preamble of each token represents the type of string:
TKN These items represent strings that can be added to the XML Documentation in a way that they will show up in the generated OAS document.
PARAM These items contain strings that represent the names of common parameters that (when used by developers in the API) will allow the OAS parser to identify these parameters as properties to make dynamioc in any generated test harnesses.
OAS These items contain strings that are known constants defined within the Open Api Spec.
DESC These items are more generic and act as a 'catch-all' bucket for terms.
